noun.description: A reimpression of a coin, medal, or print.
Electrical Engineering. An instance or the fact of an arc restriking.

verb.description: To strike again; especially to mint (a coin or coinage) again or differently.
Of an arc: to come into being again.
To bring (an arc) into being again.

origin: Late 19th century. From restrike<br>early 17th century; earliest use found in Anthony Nixon (fl. 1592–1616), pamphleteer. From re- + strike.
